{"id":3411,"date":"2016-01-08T11:17:40","date_gmt":"2016-01-08T11:17:40","guid":{"rendered":"http:\/\/jc-static-copy.local\/?p=3411"},"modified":"2026-05-17T07:47:07","modified_gmt":"2026-05-17T06:47:07","slug":"writing-longhand-a-poll","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"http:\/\/jc-static-copy.local\/writing-longhand-a-poll\/","title":{"rendered":"Writing Longhand &#8211; a poll!"},"content":{"rendered":"\n\n\t<p>I cannot write straight to screen. At least, I occasionally can for short stories or more factual pieces but when it comes to the first draft of a novel, I have to write it pen in hand. I just find that my ideas seem to flow so much more naturally if they go straight from my head, down my arm and onto the paper via a pen &#8211; almost an extension of my own hand, even &#8211; at the risk of sounding pretentious &#8211; of my own self.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"http:\/\/jc-static-copy.local\/wp-content\/uploads\/Window-Seat-pic-200x159.jpg\" alt=\"Window Seat pic\" width=\"200\" height=\"159\" \/>I find that sitting straight-backed at my computer, although wonderful for editing, just makes me feel far too much as if I&#8217;m &#8216;at work&#8217; to be truly creative. I much prefer to curl up on my sofa, or out in the sunshine (if we ever get any again!) or even, occasionally, in my bed and go for it in a great big, tactile notebook.<\/p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" src=\"http:\/\/jc-static-copy.local\/wp-content\/uploads\/office-007-200x150.jpg\" alt=\"office 007\" width=\"200\" height=\"150\" \/>It&#8217;s a bit of a nuisance as it then means I have to type it all up but I also find that an important part of the process as I do a bit of first editing as I go along. It&#8217;s only doing interviews after the publication of The Chosen Queen and talking to people at events and book groups that&#8217;s made me realise that these days I&#8217;m rather unusual in working this way. So I thought it would be really interesting to find out how others work.<\/p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re a writer and you have 10 seconds to spare (perhaps you&#8217;re looking for an excuse to dodge some tricky editing?) then click <a href=\"http:\/\/goo.gl\/naeNiJ\">HERE<\/a> and let me know if you write longhand like me, or straight to screen like most. Thank you and I look forward to the answers.<\/p>\n<p>Joanna<\/p>\n\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>I cannot write straight to screen. At least, I occasionally can for short stories or more factual pieces but when it comes to the first draft of a novel, I have to write it pen in hand. I just find that my ideas seem to flow so much more naturally if they go straight from&hellip;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":5,"featured_media":3534,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"slim_seo":{"title":"Writing Longhand - a poll! - Joanna Courtney","description":"I cannot write straight to screen. At least, I occasionally can for short stories or more factual pieces but when it comes to the first draft of a novel, I have"},"footnotes":""},"categories":[23],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-3411","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-blog"],"acf":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/jc-static-copy.local\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/3411","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/jc-static-copy.local\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"http:\/\/jc-static-copy.local\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/jc-static-copy.local\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/5"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/jc-static-copy.local\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=3411"}],"version-history":[{"count":1,"href":"http:\/\/jc-static-copy.local\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/3411\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":4735,"href":"http:\/\/jc-static-copy